cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR 

The paper deals with the segmentation of consumer stereo videos, which involves computer vision and machine learning techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a novel ensemble method based on spectral theory, which falls under the category of cs.MM (Multimedia). The use of a regressor to optimize the stereo segmentation performance directly via a differentiable proxy suggests the involvement of machine learning techniques, which could fall under the categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper deals with the segmentation of videos, which could fall under the category of cs.GR (Graphics).
